3.2 Redis Key Conventions

Key Pattern

Purpose

rate:<ip>:<endpoint>

Rate limit counter. TTL: 60s. Value: integer count.

idem:<tenantId>:<key>

Idempotency lock during in-flight request. TTL: 30s.

session:<sessionId>

Portal session (JWT claims cache). TTL: 15min.

prov:<workspaceId>

Provisioning lock — prevents duplicate realm creation. TTL: 120s.

usage:<tenantId>:<YYYY-MM>

Incrementing MAU/login counters. Flushed to Postgres nightly. TTL: 40 days.




SECTION 4

Project Structure & Developer Setup




4.1 Monorepo Folder Structure

All services live in a single repository. Each service is a self-contained folder with its own Dockerfile, package.json (or equivalent), and README. The root contains only orchestration files.

foundry-iam/

├── docker-compose.yml          # Full dev environment (all services)

├── docker-compose.prod.yml     # Production overrides

├── .env.example                # All required environment variables

├── .env                        # Local only — never commit

├── Makefile                    # Dev shortcuts (make up, make seed, make logs)

├── README.md                   # Getting started in < 5 minutes

