4.4 Makefile Shortcuts

# Makefile



up:          ## Start all services

        docker compose up --build -d



down:        ## Stop all services

        docker compose down



logs:        ## Tail all logs

        docker compose logs -f



logs-api:    ## Tail API logs

        docker compose logs -f api



migrate:     ## Run Prisma migrations

        docker compose exec api npx prisma migrate dev



seed:        ## Seed dev data (1 tenant, 1 app)

        docker compose exec api npm run seed



test:        ## Run all tests

        docker compose exec api npm test



kc-admin:    ## Open Keycloak Admin Console

        open http://localhost:8080/admin



mail:        ## Open Mailpit email UI

        open http://localhost:8025



studio:      ## Open Prisma Studio (DB GUI)

        docker compose exec api npx prisma studio



reset:       ## Destroy volumes and start fresh

        docker compose down -v && make up




SECTION 5

Keycloak Realm Template




5.1 Realm Bootstrap Sequence

When the control plane provisions a new tenant, the following sequence runs against the Keycloak Admin REST API. This is idempotent — running it twice produces the same result.

Step

API Call

Notes

1

POST /admin/realms

Create realm with all defaults applied

2

PUT /admin/realms/{realm}/ui-ext

Apply branding (logo URL, primary colour)

3

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/roles (×4)

tenant_owner, tenant_admin, tenant_billing, tenant_viewer

4

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/groups (×3)

owners, admins, billing

5

Assign roles to groups (×3)

owners→tenant_owner, admins→tenant_admin, billing→tenant_billing

6

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/clients

Create portal-mgmt (confidential, service account only)

7

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/users

Create owner user with temporary password

8

POST /admin/realms/{realm}/users/{id}/groups

Assign owner user to owners group

9

PUT /admin/realms/{realm}/users/{id}/execute-actions-email

Trigger verify + set password email



5.2 Realm Defaults

Setting

Value

registrationAllowed

false — control plane manages user creation

loginWithEmailAllowed

true

duplicateEmailsAllowed

false

verifyEmail

true

resetPasswordAllowed

true

sslRequired

external

bruteForceProtected

true

failureFactor

5 attempts before lockout

waitIncrementSeconds

60

maxFailureWaitSeconds

900 (15 min lockout)

accessTokenLifespan

900 (15 minutes)

ssoSessionIdleTimeout

28800 (8 hours)

ssoSessionMaxLifespan

86400 (24 hours)

offlineSessionIdleTimeout

2592000 (30 days)

actionTokenGeneratedByUserLifespan

300 (5 min)

internationalEnabled

true

defaultLocale

en

eventsEnabled

true

adminEventsEnabled

true

eventsExpiration

604800 (7 days in Keycloak; ship to log pipeline beyond)



5.3 Password Policy String

length(10) and digit(1) and lowerCase(1) and upperCase(1) and specialChars(1) and passwordHistory(5)



5.4 Built-in Clients

Client

Purpose

portal-mgmt

Confidential. Service accounts enabled. Used by control plane API to administer the realm. Granted minimal permissions: manage-users, view-clients. Standard flow disabled.

account-console

Keycloak built-in. Enabled for future self-service user profile management. Not linked from portal in MVP.

portal-spa (SaaS admin realm only)

Public OIDC client. Used by the Foundry IAM portal itself to authenticate our operators. Lives in the foundry-saas master realm, not in tenant realms.



5.5 Custom Token Claims

A custom protocol mapper is applied to every realm so that JWTs include platform-level context. This allows customer APIs to authorise based on claims without extra API calls.

// Claims added to every Access Token

{

  "tenant_id": "tnt_2f8a1d",

  "workspace_id": "wsp_c91b12",

  "realm_roles": ["tenant_admin", "app_user"],

  "iat": 1709120000,

  "exp": 1709120900,

  "iss": "https://id.foundry-iam.com/realms/tnt_2f8a1d",

  "sub": "<keycloak_user_uuid>"

}




