8.3 Stripe Integration

Concern

Implementation

Checkout flow

POST /v1/tenants/:id/billing/checkout returns a Stripe Checkout URL. No card data touches our servers.

Webhooks

POST /v1/webhooks/stripe handles: customer.subscription.created, customer.subscription.updated, customer.subscription.deleted, invoice.payment_failed

Plan enforcement

On subscription update, control plane updates tenant.plan. API enforces plan limits (workspace count, MAU quota warnings).

Overage billing

Monthly cron reads usage_snapshots, computes overages, creates Stripe usage records for metered billing items.

Trial

14-day free trial on Starter plan. Card required upfront (Stripe Setup Intent). Charged on day 15.




SECTION 9

Security Posture




9.1 Authentication & Authorisation

Concern

Implementation

Control plane API auth

All endpoints require valid JWT issued by the foundry-saas Keycloak realm. Validated via JWKS (RS256). Token lifetime: 15 minutes.

API key auth

SHA-256 hashed at rest. Scoped to a single tenant. Rate-limited. Displayed to user exactly once on creation.

Keycloak Admin API access

Control plane uses a dedicated service account (master realm) with minimal permissions. Credentials never exposed outside the API container.

Tenant isolation

Realm-level isolation: a compromised token from Tenant A is cryptographically invalid in Tenant B. No cross-realm validation.

Portal JWT storage

Tokens stored in memory only (oidc-client-ts). Never in localStorage, sessionStorage, or cookies.



9.2 Infrastructure Security

Keycloak Admin Console is NOT exposed on a public port. Admin API accessible only within Docker network (api → keycloak on internal DNS).

PostgreSQL is NOT exposed on a public port in production. Accessible only within Docker network.

Redis is NOT exposed on a public port in production. AUTH password enforced.

All public endpoints sit behind NGINX/Caddy with TLS termination and security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options).

Rate limiting on all endpoints: 200 req/min per IP, 10 req/min for /v1/tenants POST.

Stripe webhook signature verification: raw body + STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET. Reject any request without valid signature.

Secrets in environment variables only. No secrets in Docker images, Git, or logs.



9.3 Operational Security

Support access is time-boxed (max 1440 minutes) and audit-logged with reason. Tenant must explicitly enable.

All control plane mutations written to audit_logs table with actor, IP, timestamp, and payload hash.

Invite tokens are bcrypt-hashed at rest. Expire in 7 days. Single-use.

Brute force protection enabled on all Keycloak realms (5 failures → 15-minute lockout).

Event retention: Keycloak events kept 7 days in-database. Ship to log pipeline (Loki/Datadog) for long-term retention.




